<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="256" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,582,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">
Distribution: Indian records: Meghalaya, West Bengal (
<bibRefCitation author="Grehan, J. R. &amp; Ismavel, V. A." box="[793,1081,655,681]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="9940 - 9955" refId="ref8690" refString="Grehan, J. R. &amp; Ismavel, V. A. (2017) Forest ghost moth fauna of northeastern India (Lepidoptera: Hepialidae: Endoclita, Palpifer, and Hepialiscus). Journal of Threatened Taxa, 9 (3), 9940 - 9955. https: // doi. org / 10.11609 / jott. 3030.9.3.9940 - 9955" type="journal article" year="2017">Grehan &amp; Ismavel 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Global records: 
<collectingCountry box="[1290,1357,655,681]" name="Nepal" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Nepal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ueda, K." pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="70 - 93" refId="ref12597" refString="Ueda, K. (2000) Hepialidae. In: Haruta, T. (Ed.), Moths of Nepal. Part 6. Tinea, 16 (1), 70 - 93." type="journal article" year="2000">Ueda 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="256" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,582,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">
Note: 
<bibRefCitation author="Grehan, J. R. &amp; Mielke, C. G. C. &amp; Basu, D. N. &amp; Pawar, U. &amp; Ismavel, V. A. &amp; Rawlins, J. E. &amp; Kunte, K." box="[223,456,727,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref8927" refString="Grehan, J. R., Mielke, C. G. C., Basu, D. N., Pawar, U., Ismavel, V. A., Rawlins, J. E. &amp; Kunte, K. (2022) A new species of Endoclita C. &amp; R. Felder, 1874 ghost moth from Karimganj district of Assam, India, with comments on the genus in Northeastern India, and clarification of E. signifer (Walker, 1856) (Lepidoptera: Hepialidae). ZooNova, 16, 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="2022">
Grehan 
<emphasis box="[314,365,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">et al</emphasis>
. (2022)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned distribution of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[763,850,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Endoclita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aboe">
<emphasis box="[763,850,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">E. aboe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[923,1008,727,753]" country="India" name="Sikkim" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Sikkim</collectingRegion>
. But Moore ([1860]) in his catalogue described the species from Darjeeling which was previously under 
<collectingRegion box="[952,1033,763,789]" country="India" name="Sikkim" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Sikkim</collectingRegion>
but presently is a part of 
<collectingRegion country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ueda, K." box="[248,390,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="70 - 93" refId="ref12597" refString="Ueda, K. (2000) Hepialidae. In: Haruta, T. (Ed.), Moths of Nepal. Part 6. Tinea, 16 (1), 70 - 93." type="journal article" year="2000">Ueda (2000)</bibRefCitation>
also clarified about the presence of 
<specimenCount box="[807,937,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" type="male">eight males</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[995,1132,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
preserved in BMNH from Darjeeling only. So, we conclude that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[625,710,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Endoclita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aboe">
<emphasis box="[625,710,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">E. aboe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is, so far, reported from 
<collectingRegion box="[988,1129,835,861]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
only.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
